content: Had dinner with family. Shared my recent setback and they're more supportive than ever.
New risk management system has reduced potential losses by 15% in simulation. Still needs refinement but it's a start.
Discussing market psychology with a mentor. Learning how emotions play into trading decisions.
Joined a quantum computing workshop. It's mind-bending but crucial for understanding quantum-resistant blockchain tech.
Revisiting the trading failure with a clearer mindset. Found key areas where my strategy was flawed.
Had a breakthrough with the risk management system. It now anticipates market volatility better.
Caught up with friends from the tech community. They're excited about my new direction in trading.
Implemented a new module to analyze market sentiment. Combining tech and psychology in trading is intriguing.
The quantum computing study group is challenging but rewarding. We're exploring quantum key distribution.
Just got an invitation to present my risk management system at a local trading conference. A step forward.
